[5, "(At 40x you need to lean against a wall, or rest the monocular against something to keep it steady. You won't be able to keep still enough if you're just standing up straight. This isn't a fault of the lens - but the physics of a highly zoomed image. You're seeing an image that's about 0.5 degrees wide - about 5 meters at 200 feet. The smallest arm tremor would move more than that 5 meters...)", [3, 3, 4, 5, 18], [2, 3, 6, 11, 196]]